OL,3,CCompensation for pupils given infected
OL,4,Cblood 'nowhere near enough', says MP
OL,6,FThe Government's offer of #60,000 to
OL,7,Fformer Treloar School pupils infected
OL,8,Fwith contaminated blood "is nowhere
OL,9,Fnear enough", a Labour MP has said.
OL,11,FClive Efford, a Labour MP and chairman
OL,12,Fof the All-Party Parliamentary Group
OL,13,F(APPG) on Haemophilia and Contaminated
OL,14,FBlood, suggested the payments do not
OL,15,Faddress the gravity of the situation.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
